article_metadata.description: Like other Republican presidential candidates, Gov. John Kasich has promised to repeal and replace Obamacare if elected, begging the question: With what? He has yet to offer a proposal with enough detail to analyze how well it might work. But Kasich’s team in state government has developed a plan for Ohio that he says could be applied to the entire country.
